revenues  the decrease in game sales and subscriptions revenue reflected a 29% decrease from lower console game unit sales and a 8% decrease from lower net effective pricing of console games reflecting the strong
performance of lego pirates of the caribbean, cars 2 and epic mickey in the prior-year period. the decrease was partially offset by an 11% increase from higher social games revenue reflecting improved title performance in the
current period and lower acquisition accounting impacts.  higher advertising and other revenue was driven by an increase at
our mobile phone service in japan which included a benefit from higher rates.  costs and expenses
