marketing costs at our domestic parks and resorts, costs associated with the addition of the disney dream and aulani, our new resort in hawaii, and labor cost inflation.  segment operating income  segment operating income increased 18%, or $235
million, to $1.6 billion due to increases at our domestic parks and resorts and hong kong disneyland resort, partially offset by costs for aulani and a decrease at tokyo disney resort.
