a significant portion of the assets of the companys defined benefit plans are managed on a commingled basis in a third-party master
trust. the investment policy and allocation of the assets in the master trust were approved by the companys investment and administrative committee which has oversight responsibility for the companys retirement plans. the investment
policy ranges for the major asset classes are as follows:
