$10.96, and $9.43, respectively. the total intrinsic value (market value on date of exercise less exercise price) of options exercised and rsus vested during 2012, 2011, and 2010 totaled $1,033 million, $969 million, and $830 million, respectively.
the aggregate intrinsic values of stock options vested and expected to vest at september29, 2012 were $614 million and $424 million, respectively.  as of september29, 2012, there was $158 million of unrecognized compensation cost related to unvested stock options and $573 million related to unvested rsus. that cost is expected to be recognized
over a weighted-average period of 1.7 years for stock options and 1.7 years for rsus.
